<br>
Assuming the druid debuffs are all cast by the same druid, or druids of the same level:<br>
<br>
1) Cast RFS to lower mob fire resist, and to help you land the next 2 debuffs<br>
2) Cast Fixation.  This stacks.<br>
3) Cast RSD.  This overwrites RFS, and is basically an upgrade.  Again, it's important to cast RFS first so Fixate and RSD stick more easily.<br>
4) Cast Breath of Ro.  This further debuffs the mob, stacks.<br>
5) I have not tried stacking immolate with Fixate, RSD, and BoR.  It hardly seems worth it, when I have back-up healing, etc to deal with.  Someone wanna comment on this?<br>
<br>
So when I'm done, the mob is Fixated (ac/attk debuff), Dysjunctioned (Fire resist debuff), Breathed (more FR debuff, more melee debuff), and theoretically, could be immolated too... but I'd never tried.  RFS has been overwritten by RSD, but it served its purpose by helping to stick the first two fire-based debuffs.<br>
<br>
There are stacking issues that arise when druids of different levels try to stack debuffs.  I won't go into it because it makes my head hurt, but as a general rule, don't try it.<br>
<br>
