<br>
CASE A:<br>
- Sundering<br>
- Fixation<br>
- Disjunction (this overwrite Sundering)<br>
<br>
CASE B: (not realistic)<br>
- Fixation<br>
- Sundering<br>
- Disjunction (this overwrite Fixtation)<br>
<br>
Short and sweet, Sundering gives you a whopping dose of fire-debuff, Fixation gives you a good dose of mele-debuff, and Disjunction gives you a dose of each (twice as good!).<br>
<br>
So, because of what you're overwriting, you get:<br>
<br>
CASE A: 2 x Mele-Debuff, 1 x Fire-Debuff<br>
CASE B: 1 x Mele-Debuff, 2 x Fire-Debuff<br>
<br>
Of course, you're actually getting an extra boost to fire debuff with Breath of Ro in either of the cases.<br>
